to maintain, and furnish to the Minister, periodic reports, records, returns, samples and data concerning petroleum operations;
(c) to keep current financial and cost accounting records of petroleum operations, with pertinent records and vouchers, during the term of the contract, in accordance with normal accounting practices in the international petroleum industry;
