(1) No person shall, without the written consent of the President, carry out petroleum operations— (a) upon any land dedicated as a place of burial; (b) upon any land containing any ancient monument or national monument as defined in the National Heritage Conservation Commission Act; [ Cap. 173 ] (c) upon any land which is the site of or is within one hundred metres of any building or dam owned by the Republic; (d) upon any land forming part of a Government aerodrome as defined in the Air Navigation Regulations; [Cap. 444] (e) upon any land occupied as a village; or (f) upon any land forming part of a defence establishment.
